description:
Expansive 1 Bedroom with Sweeping City and Water Views!

The Residence:
• Breathtaking Views 
• Expansive Open-Concept Layout
• Gorgeous Modern Finishes
• In-Unit Laundry
• High End Appliances
• Hardwood Floors
• Central Air

The Building: 

Welcome to Tower 77, where contemporary luxury meets the vibrant energy of Brooklyn's Greenpoint neighborhood. Nestled within the heart of one of Brooklyn's most sought-after locales, this iconic tower offers an unparalleled living experience.

Boasting stunning architectural design and panoramic views of the Manhattan skyline and East River, Tower 77 stands as a beacon of modernity in the historic landscape of Greenpoint. With its sleek glass facade and meticulously crafted interiors, this residence sets a new standard for urban living. There's a home to suit every lifestyle.

Beyond the apartments, Tower 77 offers an array of amenities designed to enhance your daily life. 
• Stay active in the state-of-the-art fitness center and yoga studios
• Bring some friends to enjoy a Tennis Match or Basketball Game followed by a Barbecue on one of Two Terraces
• Host gatherings in the stylish resident lounge, children's playroom, media room, co working space, or recreational area. 
• We also boast one of the best, state of the art sauna and pool areas with spectacular terrace access to breathtaking water and city views.

The Neighborhood:

Conveniently located just moments away from the vibrant dining, shopping, and entertainment options of Greenpoint, Tower 77 provides residents with easy access to everything this dynamic neighborhood has to offer. With nearby transportation options including the G train and East River Ferry, Manhattan is just a short commute away.

Large, Contemporary One Bedroom Located in an Elevator Building in Hudson Heights

Residence

Welcome to this contemporary, nearly floor-through one-bedroom, beautifully illuminated with natural light and situated in an elevator building west of Broadway. This residence features an expansive layout with high ceilings and gorgeous hardwood floors, creating an elegant and sophisticated atmosphere. The bright and spacious bedroom is secluded from the rest of the apartment and offers ample closet space, pleasant street views, and is designed to accommodate a bed plus additional furniture comfortably.

Building & Location

With a long gated entry and an impressively renovated lobby, This building is located on West 181st and Fort Washington – arguably the best location in Washington Heights. With multiple transportation options just moments away including the A, C, and 1 trains, you are never far from the vibrant food scene of the neighborhood. The serene and well-maintained Bennett Park is only a few blocks away, perfect for a morning jog or a leisurely evening stroll. The building’s proximity to the George Washington Bridge is an added advantage for those who enjoy driving out of the city.
